Convert an object to list with identical structure

Source: R/helpers.R
list_parse.Rd

This functions are similar to rlist::list.parse but this removes names. NA's are removed for compatibility with rjson::toJSON.

list_parse(df)

list_parse2(df)

Arguments

df

A data frame to parse to list

Examples


x <- data.frame(a = 1:3, type = c("A", "C", "B"), stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
list_parse(x)
#> [[1]]
#> [[1]]$a
#> [1] 1
#> 
#> [[1]]$type
#> [1] "A"
#> 
#> 
#> [[2]]
#> [[2]]$a
#> [1] 2
#> 
#> [[2]]$type
#> [1] "C"
#> 
#> 
#> [[3]]
#> [[3]]$a
#> [1] 3
#> 
#> [[3]]$type
#> [1] "B"
#> 
#> 
list_parse2(x)
#> [[1]]
#> [[1]][[1]]
#> [1] 1
#> 
#> [[1]][[2]]
#> [1] "A"
#> 
#> 
#> [[2]]
#> [[2]][[1]]
#> [1] 2
#> 
#> [[2]][[2]]
#> [1] "C"
#> 
#> 
#> [[3]]
#> [[3]][[1]]
#> [1] 3
#> 
#> [[3]][[2]]
#> [1] "B"
#> 
#>
